ol.li:
To convert from polar coordinates (r, \theta) to Cartesian: 
      \begin{align*}
        x \amp = r\cos \theta\\
        y \amp = r \sin \theta\\
        \end{align*}

To convert from Cartesian coordinates (x,y) to polar:
    \begin{align*}
        \amp r = \sqrt{x^2+y^2}\\
        \amp \tan \theta = \dfrac{y}{x}\\
        \end{align*}

To convert from polar coordinates (r, \theta) to Cartesian: 
      \begin{align*}
        x \amp = r\cos \theta\\
        y \amp = r \sin \theta\\
        \end{align*}

To convert from Cartesian coordinates (x,y) to polar:
    \begin{align*}
        \amp r = \sqrt{x^2+y^2}\\
        \amp \tan \theta = \dfrac{y}{x}\\
        \end{align*}
